The course considers the contextualized approaches to child development.  The influence of the environment at the early stages of child's development.  Analysis of the influence of modern culture on child's development (TV, ads, computer and video games).Objectives/eesmärkid:  To acquaint students with the peculiarities of physical, social and cultural environment influence on young learners.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: 1) is aware of contextual approaches to child's development; 2) has knowledge about environment influences on child's early years development; 3) is able to design and organise a physical environment considering children's peculiarities; 4) can analyse the impact of the aspects of modern culture on a child's consciousness; 5) can counsel parents on the issues of creating a physical and cultural environment; 6) is able to create a democratic and physically and mentally secure environment which supports learning and learner's development.
